 at the Office of Hearing Examiners. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 10-11 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any shareholder of a subchapter S corporation may represent the corporation during a property tax appeal, pursuant to chapter 10-11, to the Officer of Hearing Examiners. No subchapter S corporation may be required to be represented by an attorney during the property tax appeal before the Officer of Hearing Examiners. 180 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.063 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 3419, "bill_version_id": 20396, "bill_version": "Senate Taxation Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2012-01-30T13:33:01.527-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow shareholders or officers of South Dakota corporations or subchapter S corporations to represent the corporation in property tax appeals at the Office of Hearing Examiners. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 10-11 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any shareholder or officer of a South Dakota corporation or a subchapter S corporation may represent the corporation during a property tax appeal, pursuant to chapter 10-11, to the Officer of Hearing Examiners. No South Dakota corporation or subchapter S corporation may be required to be represented by an attorney during the property tax appeal before the Officer of Hearing Examiners. 180 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.063 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 3419, "bill_version_id": 20722, "bill_version": "Senate Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2012-02-02T16:43:19.043-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow officers of corporations to represent corporations in property tax appeals at the Office of Hearing Examiners. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 10-11 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: Any officer of a corporation may represent the corporation during a property tax appeal, pursuant to chapter 10-11, to the Officer of Hearing Examiners. No corporation may be required to be represented by an attorney during the property tax appeal before the Officer of Hearing Examiners. 180 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.063 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 3419, "bill_version_id": 22104, "bill_version": "House Judiciary Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2012-02-24T15:25:17.123-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow officers of corporations to represent corporations in property tax appeals at the Office of Hearing Examiners. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 10-11 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: After notice and unanimous vote of the shareholders, a shareholder of a subchapter S corporation that has ten or fewer shareholders, may represent the corporation during a property tax appeal, pursuant to chapter 10-11, to the Office of Hearing Examiners. The designated shareholder does not need to be a licensed attorney. In order to exercise this option, the corporation shall present to the Office of Hearing Examiners, the name and mailing address of each of the shareholders, proof of notice to the shareholders, and a copy of the minutes and motion or resolution reflecting the unanimous vote authorizing the designated shareholder to represent the corporation in the appeal. 180 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.063 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 3419, "bill_version_id": 22577, "bill_version": "Conference Committee Engrossed", "bill_version_date": "2012-03-02T12:03:17.623-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to allow shareholders of corporations to represent corporations in property tax appeals at the Office of Hearing Examiners. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. That chapter 10-11 be amended by adding thereto a NEW SECTION to read as follows: After notice and unanimous vote of the shareholders, a shareholder of a subchapter S corporation that has ten or fewer shareholders, may represent the corporation during a property tax appeal, pursuant to chapter 10-11, to the Office of Hearing Examiners. The designated shareholder does not need to be a licensed attorney. In order to exercise this option, the corporation shall present to the Office of Hearing Examiners, the name and mailing address of each of the shareholders, proof of notice to the shareholders, and a copy of the minutes and motion or resolution reflecting the unanimous vote authorizing the designated shareholder to represent the corporation in the appeal. 180 copies were printed on recycled paper by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.063 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}, {"bill_id": 3419, "bill_version_id": 22578, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2012-03-02T12:05:18.277-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 3419, "action_date": "2012-01-23T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 19958